
Possible hints for installing the requirements for various distributions:

Debian and Debian derivatives:
apt-get install python-django python-dulwich barcode qrencode sam2p w3m

Fedora:
yum install Django python-dulwich barcode qrencode w3m python-imaging

Opensuse:
zypper in python-django barcode qrencode w3m python-imaging python-dulwich

Fedora/Opensuse users will also need to download the sam2p binary for Linux 
from http://code.google.com/p/sam2p/downloads/list, extract the file, and 
place it manually in /usr/local/bin.

Mandriva/Mageia:
urpmi python-django barcode qrencode w3m python-imaging sam2p

Mandriva/Mageia users will need to install python-dulwich from source, as 
outlined in 00README.

